The adapted material includes the small partial-pivoting LU solver and the
hessian-weighted per-leaf linear-model design introduced in ChimeraBoost
commits 425dfb316fcfb39538ccbe3794455e9ca6cf9e04,
832e7a202aea32c588598b9297e58be64fd95223, and
ce5ca0d6ed324f16c1973b366663e0fe29ea3c03. DarkoFit integrates those ideas
with its own row-major tree kernels, sampling semantics, model format,
flattened prediction path, and validation/refit policy.

The feature-parallel fused histogram-build/shared-split design and small-row
serial leaf-descent dispatch are adapted from ChimeraBoost commit
a04430657fb82c806ee2a039506c99944a27accc. DarkoFit preserves its own
row-major buffers, split-legality semantics, floating-point order, and
existing kernels as exact-equality references.

The exact interventional TreeSHAP coalition-enumeration algorithm is adapted
from ChimeraBoost commit ff6f248d09f92d608ed8cc366463b61f1af04acc.
DarkoFit modifies it for row-major binned data, its serialized empirical
background, original-feature grouping, and its local-linear leaf format.

The explicit startup warmup API and opt-in environment dispatch are adapted
from ChimeraBoost commit 851ab7fa79fbb2a7f698fbc1a00952e1bd18c62d.
DarkoFit uses its own default-path synthetic fits, thread restoration, and
coverage boundary.

The public input-validation and scikit-learn compliance layer adapts the
masked/complex/non-finite checks, named categorical resolution, feature-name
enforcement, nullable frame coercion, and ``assume_finite`` serving escape
hatch from ChimeraBoost commit
851ab7fa79fbb2a7f698fbc1a00952e1bd18c62d. DarkoFit centralizes those
behaviors across its sklearn wrappers, scalar and multiclass boosters, and
distributional heads while preserving its existing model format.

The benchmark-only ``benchmarks/synthgen`` structural-causal-model generator,
calibration sampler, deterministic dataset emission, freeze-time filters,
suite selection, and generator contract tests are modified from ChimeraBoost
0.15.0 commit 851ab7fa79fbb2a7f698fbc1a00952e1bd18c62d. DarkoFit adds its own
version namespace, removes TabArena and all declared CTR23 identities before
calibration reduction, verifies canaries with DarkoFit, and uses a separate
project-specific decision ledger and adoption protocol.

The benchmark-only packed-int64 quantization microprototype adapts
ChimeraBoost's gradient/Hessian packing and counter-based stochastic-rounding
design from commit f14be606b641f1bf0dc92bb14b3951f1fe631c6b. DarkoFit's
prototype uses its own row-major histogram shape, exact unit-Hessian count,
split-legality semantics, post-dispatch control, and funding analysis.
